      "updated": 1763817935585,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. partition key: either it be userId or something else. It is the one that makes system scalable.\n Wrong key might overload the system and create hot parition key. \n2. offsets are maintained in kafka for fault tolerance. If some consumer goes down also, then also we will have something to\nread data from. That is kafka dedicated topic named as offset something.\n3. there are some ISR(in sync replicas) and some are not. These replicas which are ISR are made leaders in case something goes down. \n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. partition key: either it be userId or something else. It is the one that makes system scalable.\n Wrong key might overload the system and create hot parition key. \n2. offsets are maintained in kafka for fault tolerance. If some consumer goes down also, then also we will have something to\nread data from. That is kafka dedicated topic named as offset something.\n3. there are some ISR(in sync replicas) and some are not. These replicas which are ISR are made leaders in case something goes down. \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BQMjwP--i5baXfq8iU-dO",
      "type": "text",
